Bonus problems.

Make Description:
   Type "make" to compile the code.

Part (a) has been implemented.

The refraction feature only works for the user scence, so use -u to test.

chess_scene.png is run with the command ./raychess –u 5 +s +l +r +c +p .

Test Command:
1. Ray-chess intersection and local reflectance.
   ./raychess [–u | –d] 0
2. Shadows.
   ./raychess [–u | –d] 0 +s
3. Reflections.
   ./raychess [–u | –d] step_max +s +l
   For example,
   ./raychess [–u | –d] 5 +s +l
4. Chess board.
   ./raychess [–u | –d] step_max +s +l +c
   For example,
   ./raychess [–u | –d] 5 +s +l +c
5. Refraction.
   ./raychess –u step_max +s +l +r +c
   For example,
   ./raychess –u 5 +s +l +r +c
6. Diffuse reflections using stochastic ray generation.
   ./raychess –u step_max +s +l +r +c +f
   For example,
   ./raychess –u 5 +s +l +r +c +f
7. Supersampling to reduce aliasing.
   ./raychess –u step_max +s +l +r +f +c +p
   For example,
   ./raychess –u 5 +s +l +r +f +c +p
   This step costs some minutes.
